==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wheatworm
<hw>Wheat"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small nematode
worm (<spn>Tylenchus tritici</spn>, formerly <spn>Anguillula
tritici</spn>) which attacks wheat, advancing through the stem to the
grains in the ear. In wheat affected with smut, each of the diseased
grains may contain a large number of the minute young of the
worm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheder</ent>⟦br⟧
